tip.text: Breathtaking view.. bluefin and yellowtail jalapeño were great as usual .. the rest of he dishes  were disappointing (tacos and new style and the lobster ceviche)..
Just had to leave he tip before I've left the joint .. hands down the best burger I've had in California .perfect patty and fries and the dip sauces and ketchup are out of this world .. .
Fantastic well presented and different breakfast combinations
Walked in for lunch.. great service by the staff especially Byron .. had oysters, zucchini and the soft shell crab and shrimp tacos ...
The Burgundy was great and so was the frenchie ..
Great burger and mean fries but house rules quite anal. They can't change ingredients or add them and they don't entertain sauce requests even if only on the size
Not Instagram worthy but yummy.. had the crab cake Benedict with a side of fruits and the vanilla latte (huge)..
Michelin ⭐️ level ... presentation and taste ..
